<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06078056 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06078056 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  GREECE; ARREST; MAN; SUSPECT; PAST; BOAT; TERRORISM  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Greece has detained a man convicted in absentia by an Italian court forhelping plan the 1985 hijacking of the Achille Lauro cruise ship, a seniorpolice official confirmed today.;    Abdulrahim Khaled was arrested March 7along with three Greeks when a police search turned up dynamite and a gasolinebomb at the home of one of those detained with him, the official said.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ARAB CONVICTED IN ACHILLE LAURO HIJACKINGIS DETAINED IN GREECE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Turmoil in the Mideast  </MEMO><TEXT>     A security police spokesman said Italy had not yet requested extradition ofthe 56-year-old Khaled. Sunday, the Italian news agency ANSA quotedunidentified sources in the prosecutor's office in Genoa as saying thegovernment would ask for Khaled.;    Khaled was convicted and sentenced inabsentia to life in prison by an appeals court in Genoa in 1987 for thehijacking, during which Leon Klinghoffer, an elderly wheelchair-bound man fromNew York, was shot to death and his body thrown overboard.;    Khaled, aYemeni, is considered a colonel in Abul Abbas' Palestine Liberation Frontterrorist group.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Athens, Greece  </CITY><EDITION>  Street  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910318  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  166  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday March 18, 199100078056,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>